ife isn't worth living, unless it is lived for someone else.\n\n- Albert\n|\nCome friends, it's not too late to seek a newer world.\n\n- Alfred\n|\nHis priority did not seem to be to teach them what he knew, but rather to impress upon them that nothing, not even... knowledge, was foolproof.\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix\n|\nLincoln on a desire to hear Horace Greeley speak: 'In print, every one of his words seems to weigh about a ton.\n\n- Harold Holzer, Lincoln and the Power of the Press: The War for Public Opinion\n|\nOur state cannot be severed, we are one,One flesh; to lose thee were to lose myself.\n\n- John Milton, Paradise Lost\n|\nThe truth may be out there, but the lies are inside your head.\n\n- Terry\n|\nYou'll be okay. No matter what shape reality takes, you can handle it.\n\n- Shiro Amano, Kingdom Hearts, Vol. 1\n|\nI am so tired, I can hardly type these worfs.\n\n- Lemony Snicket, The Carnivorous Carnival\n|\nBefore she continued her search she sat in his revolving desk chair, and wept for the passing of time, and the necessary death of the well-loved, wise old man.\n\n- Robertson Davies, Tempest-Tost\n|\nCombinations of people, who should have nothing to say to each other. Yet, with hearts that do not recognize it.\n\n- Tracy Rees, Amy Snow\n|\nOnce you feel nice about yourself, you have planted the first seed to develop self-confidence.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Develop Jedi Self-Confidence: Unleash the Force within You\n|\nI gradually realized that I was seeing another example of creative ebb, another step by another art on the road that may indeed end in extinction.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nYou can never play a part in life, especially not in love.\n\n- Sarah Jio, The Bungalow\n|\nWhatsoever a man soweth, that shall he also reap.\n\n- Anonymous, Holy Bible: King James Version\n|\nProperly read, the Bible is the most potent force for atheism ever conceived.\n\n- Isaac\n|\nDon't live the same day over and over again and call that a life. Life is about evolving mentally, spiritually, and emotionally.\n\n- Germany\n|\nIt's amazing what people do for love, but the most astonishing fact is how love transforms people...\n\n- Ramana\n|\nA man who tells you to follow him will turn his followers into his company, while a true leader who does not tell you to follow him, will sit in the company of his followers.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\ntime made me stronger, you're no longer on my mind\n\n- Boyz\n|\nWith heaven in our hearts,life is romancing uswith glimpses ofthe universe dancing.\n\n- Ann\n|\nGreat books are great in part because of what they ask of their readers: they are not readily encountered, easily assessed.\n\n- Alan Jacobs, The Pleasures of Reading in an Age of Distraction\n|\nHelp us to be true, Lord. Help us to stand.\n\n- Stephen King, The Stand\n|\nAnd remember that within every lie, there is a truth hidden. Know the truth to defeat the lie.\n\n- T.A. Miles, Raventide\n|\nIf God has given us life, He is capable of any other thing.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWe are all worms, But I do believe that I am a glow worm.\n\n- Winston S. Churchill, Never Give In!: The Best of Winston Churchill's Speeches\n|\nFor you to maximize time, you want to make sure that every second of the day that comes is converted into some products.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nOne passes through the world knowing few, if any, of the important things about even the people with whom one has been from time to time in the closest intimacy.\n\n- Anthony Powell, The Kindly Ones\n|\nPeople want things to be complicated, but they have to love themselves first and then each other and then it will seed everywhere\n\n- Elizabeth Taylor-Wey, Earth: The Toughest Bootcamp in the Universe\n|\nI seem to know a lot about myself, but can’t tell who I am.\n\n- Stefan Emunds, The Priest Whisperer\n|\n