n everything. That's what education's all about.\n\n- David Eddings, Belgarath the Sorcerer\n|\nIf you try to change it, you will ruin it. Try to hold it, and you will lose it.\n\n- Lao Tzu, Tao Te Ching\n|\nI find that love is confusing, lust is always definitive.\n\n- Carl\n|\nIf it weren't for music, I would think that love is mortal.\n\n- Mark Helprin, A Soldier of the Great War\n|\nThere's no way you can wake up today, only to repeat yesterday's routine, and except better results tomorrow. Change is a must or growth is impossible.\n\n- Tyconis\n|\nChoose thy friends like thy books, few but choice\n\n- Howell\n|\nSocrates: This man, on one hand, believes that he knows something, while not knowing [anything]. On the other hand, I – equally ignorant – do not believe [that I know anything].\n\n- Plato, Apology\n|\nTo enhance and expand your vision, get an education.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThere was a lot they didn’t tell you about death, she had discovered, and one of the biggies was how long it took the ones you loved most to die in your heart.\n\n- Stephen King, Lisey's Story\n|\nGreat leaders create more leaders, not followers.\n\n- Roy T. Bennett, The Light in the Heart\n|\nI have never seen a strong and better weapon as truth. When you are honest you will just love it. People are afraid of the truth because of its sharpness, that’s why they’re liars.\n\n- Simon\n|\nYou will die, and I, and all we can create—why not a city? But if there is one thing that deserves to be immortal, it is knowledge.\n\n- John Brunner, The Crucible of Time\n|\nServe the Lord with what you have — your substance, strength, knowledge, and ability\n\n- Sunday\n|\nIf you find yourself wondering if you can go on, remember how much you’ve accomplished. Then raise your head high and be proud. YOU GOT THIS!\n\n- J.D.\n|\nPhilosophers can debate the meaning of life, but you need a Lord who can declare the meaning of life.\n\n- Max Lucado, Traveling Light: Releasing the Burdens You Were Never Inten